content.paragraph1: Visual Basic is a name for a family of programming languages from Microsoft. It may refer to:
content.ul1:
Visual Basic (classic), the original Visual Basic supported from 1991â€“2008
Visual Basic .NET (now simply referred to as "Visual Basic"), the current version of Visual Basic launched in 2002 which runs on .NET
